It is quite consistent with the nature of the subject to suppose, that the reason why Napier’s book of the Logistic of concrete quantities by concrete numbers termi- nates abrnptly, and why no other fragment of it could be found„ was, that at this stage of his speculations, he had set himself to the invention of Logarithms, which may indeed be considered as the grand result of the Logistic of concrete quantities by concrete numbers.
